<!-- ==================================== ST-50 Power Armor =====================================-->


<ThingDef ParentName="ArmorMachineableBase">
<defName>DRKApparelST50PowerArmor</defName>
<label>ST-50 Power Armor</label>
<description>The T-50 Power Armor was an early and rare prototype designed by West Tek right before what became the T-51b. Too promising for its time, and too complicated to maintain, this line never reached the final production stage. A very few number were scavenged after the Great War, mostly by Brotherhood of Steel salvage teams, in a very elementary state. 
In 2242, during the first conflict with a group known as the Enclave, the T-50 was given a second breath, serving as a frame to incorporate retro-engineered technologies and extend its capabilities.
The main microfusion reactor was replaced by dual fusion core, more reliable and capable of delivering a greater output, up to 90 kiloWatts. Armors plates were reshaped to hold a greater proportion of composites instead of metal, and silver coating was reinforced on critical parts. 
Dozens of ST-50 were experimentally produced, almost handmade, some of them given to the most experienced knights. As the Brotherhood was gaining military advantage over the Enclave, advanced power armors models became more widely available, and once again, the ST-50 became obsolete.

This one is a true piece of history.</description>

<techLevel>Spacer</techLevel>


